  "url": "https://www.ada.lk/breaking_news/\u0d85\u0db0\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dab-\u0d87\u0db8\u0dad\u0dd2-\u0d9a\u0ddd\u0da0\u0dca\u0da0\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca-\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db4\u0db1\u0dba\u0da7/11-394803",
  "time_ut": 1656132840,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0db0\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dab \u0d87\u0db8\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0ddd\u0da0\u0dca\u0da0\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0dba\u0dcf\u0db4\u0db1\u0dba\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Minister of Justice to Jaffna by train",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Dr. Wijayadasa, President's Counsel, Minister of Justice, Prison Affairs and Constitutional Reforms, to participate in a number of programs organized by institutions under the Ministry of Justice, Prisons and Constitutional Affairs with a view to furthering the services rendered to the people of the Jaffna District in the Northern Province. Mr. Rajapaksa and other Ministry officials and heads of relevant institutions arrived in Jaffna yesterday (24).",
        "The Office of the Missing Persons, the Office of Compensation and the Office for National Unity and Reconciliation under the Ministry of Justice have organized several programs for the welfare of the people in the Jaffna District of the Northern Province and the Minister of Justice has been involved in several programs of the Sinhala Hindu Friendship Association. The purpose of the trip to Jaffna.",
        "Speaking to the media after his visit to Jaffna, the Minister of Justice stated that action should be taken to adopt a new constitution, especially after the passage of the 21st Amendment to the Constitution, and that it should be carried out in a manner that promotes national unity and the rule of law to establish democracy. The Minister also stated that the dominance should be secured.",
        "Inaugurating his visit to Jaffna, the Minister of Justice said that unity, brotherhood among all nations should be further enhanced and equality of services including public service should be achieved.",
        "The Office of the Missing Persons, the Office of Compensation and the Office for National Unity and Reconciliation have organized several programs for the welfare of the people in the Jaffna District of the Northern Province. The Minister also stated that.",
        "The Office of National Unity and Reconciliation has been established to promote inter-ethnic harmony, peace and reconciliation in the aftermath of the war in Sri Lanka.",
        "Carrying out welfare activities for the families of the people who went missing during the war",
        "The Compensation Office and the Office of the Disappeared have been established to deal with compensation and property damaged by the war."
      ],
